item.title: Counting stars
item.description: Lately, I’ve been, I’ve been losing sleep Dreaming about the things that we could be But baby, I’ve been, I’ve been praying hard, Said, no more counting dollars We’ll be counting stars, yeah we’ll be counting stars I see this life like a swinging vine Swing my heart across the line In my face is flashing signs Seek it out and ye shall find Old, but I’m not that old Young, but I’m not that bold I don’t think the world is sold I’m just doing what we’re told
